title.narrative: CAPACITY FOR DELIVERY & OF NEWBORN AND INFANT HEALTH SERVICES

description.narrative: Health systems have improved capacity for the delivery and utilization of quality newborn and infant health services at the facility and community levels., which contributes to Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence, Immunization Services As Part Of Primary Health Care, Operations Support To Programme Delivery, Promotion Of Care, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being And Justice, Protection From Violence, Exploitation, Abuse And Neglect, Strengthening Primary Health Care And High-Impact Health Interventions, Strengthening Primary Health Care And High-Impact Health Interventions (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2025, parents and children, with a focus on the most vulnerable, have access to equitable, integrated, quality essential health, nutrition and HIV services including during emergencies.

title.narrative: Health systems have improved capacity for the delivery and utilization of quality newborn and infant health services at thefacility and community levels.

description.narrative: UNICEF has worked closely with Ministry of Health and NGOs providing programmatic technical and financial support, as well as provision of essential health supplies and commodities to improve the capacity of 24 health facilities and 417;Rural Health Motivators (RHM) to deliver quality health services to 46,922 newborns and infants and 33,082 mothers at the facility and community levels, through training, mentorship, innovation, procurement of vaccines and essential drugs, information sharing and promoting Primary Health Care (PHC) and health financing including during the COVID-119 pandemic and the civil unrest.; | Status:On-track | As-of Date:10/01/2022
